                TITLE: LOW COST ECG & HEART MONITORING SYSTEM USING AD8232 SENSOR

The Low-Cost ECG and Heart Monitoring System Using AD8232 Sensor is a healthcare monitoring solution designed to measure and analyze the electrical activity of the human heart in real time. 
The system uses the AD8232 ECG sensor module along with a microcontroller to acquire, process, and display Electrocardiogram (ECG) signals. 
The collected heart data can be monitored locally or transmitted to a cloud platform for remote healthcare applications.
This project provides an affordable and portable alternative to traditional ECG machines, making it suitable for continuous cardiac monitoring, home healthcare, fitness tracking, and telemedicine applications.

🎯 OBJECTIVES:
Monitor heart activity using ECG signals.
Measure heart rate in real time.
Detect abnormal heart rhythms and irregularities.
Provide continuous cardiac monitoring.
Enable remote healthcare monitoring through IoT.
Develop a low-cost and portable healthcare solution.

🛠 HARDWARE COMPONENTS:
AD8232 ECG Sensor Module
Arduino Uno
ECG Electrodes
Buzzer (Alert System)
Power Supply/Battery
Jumper Wires and Breadboard

💻 SOFTWARE TOOLS: 
Arduino IDE
Visual Studio Code

⚙️WORKING PRINCIPLE:
ECG electrodes are attached to the patient's body.
The AD8232 sensor captures electrical signals generated by the heart.
The sensor filters and amplifies the weak ECG signals.
The microcontroller reads the ECG data.
Heart rate and ECG waveform are calculated and displayed.
Data can be uploaded to the cloud for remote monitoring.
Alerts are generated if abnormal heart conditions are detected.

